
Overview of noun heartbeat

The noun heartbeat has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) pulse, pulsation, heartbeat, beat -- (the rhythmic contraction and expansion of the arteries with each beat of the heart; "he could feel the beat of her heart")
2. blink of an eye, flash, heartbeat, instant, jiffy, split second, trice, twinkling, wink, New York minute -- (a very short time (as the time it takes the eye to blink or the heart to beat); "if I had the chance I'd do it in a flash")
3. heartbeat -- (an animating or vital unifying force; "New York is the commercial heartbeat of America")
